definitions.definition: To flow out, to proceed from, to come out or from.
examples: The water issued forth from the spring.
The rents issuing from the land permitted him to live as a man of independent means.

definitions.definition: To rush out, to sally forth.
examples: The men issued from the town and attacked the besiegers.

definitions.definition: To extend into, to open onto.
examples: The road issues into the highway.

definitions.definition: To turn out in a certain way , to result in.
To end up as, to turn out being, to become as a result.
To come to a point in fact or law on which the parties join issue.
To send out; to put into circulation.
examples: The Federal Reserve issues US dollars.
The prison issued new uniforms for the inmates.
The court issued a writ of mandamus.
